<h2>How to take screenshot on Asus Zenfone 3 Using the screenshot button</h2>
<p>
  For capturing the screenshot using this method, you need to customise in the
  quick settings option. This is one time settings.
</p>
<p>
  <img
    src="How-to-take-screenshot-on-Asus-Zenfone-3-Using-the-screenshot-button.png"
    alt="How to take screenshot on Asus Zenfone 3 Using the screenshot button"
    width="800"
    height="450"
  />
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    Go to quick setting options which you can access by swiping down on the home
    screen.
  </li>
  <li>Now tap on to edit(2nd icon from the top right).</li>
  <li>
    Under “Select tools to show on quick settings panel”, enable “screenshot” by
    dragging it.
  </li>
  <li>
    As you can select only 4 tools, you might need to disable any of one of the
    currently showing tool.
  </li>
  <li>
    Now whenever you want to take screenshot, go to quick settings panel and tap
    on to screenshot button.
  </li>
  <li>The screenshot will be captured.</li>
  <li>Taken screenshots will be saved in phone gallery automatically.</li>
</ul>
